15/*! \file */
16
17#include <config.h>
18
19#include <isccfg/cfg.h>
20#include <isccfg/grammar.h>
21
22/*%
23 * A trusted key, as used in the "trusted-keys" statement.
24 */
25static cfg_tuplefielddef_t trustedkey_fields[] = {
26 { "name", &cfg_type_astring, 0 },
27 { "flags", &cfg_type_uint32, 0 },
28 { "protocol", &cfg_type_uint32, 0 },
29 { "algorithm", &cfg_type_uint32, 0 },
30 { "key", &cfg_type_qstring, 0 },
31 { NULL, NULL, 0 }
32};
33
34static cfg_type_t cfg_type_trustedkey = {
35 "trustedkey", cfg_parse_tuple, cfg_print_tuple, cfg_doc_tuple,
36 &cfg_rep_tuple, trustedkey_fields
37};
38
39static cfg_type_t cfg_type_trustedkeys = {
40 "trusted-keys", cfg_parse_bracketed_list, cfg_print_bracketed_list,
41 cfg_doc_bracketed_list, &cfg_rep_list, &cfg_type_trustedkey
42};
43
44/*%
45 * Clauses that can be found within the top level of the dns.conf
46 * file only.
47 */
48static cfg_clausedef_t
49dnsconf_clauses[] = {
50 { "trusted-keys", &cfg_type_trustedkeys, CFG_CLAUSEFLAG_MULTI },
51 { NULL, NULL, 0 }
52};
53
54/*% The top-level dns.conf syntax. */
55
56static cfg_clausedef_t *
57dnsconf_clausesets[] = {
58 dnsconf_clauses,
59 NULL
60};
61
62LIBISCCFG_EXTERNAL_DATA cfg_type_t cfg_type_dnsconf = {
63 "dnsconf", cfg_parse_mapbody, cfg_print_mapbody, cfg_doc_mapbody,
64 &cfg_rep_map, dnsconf_clausesets
65};
